2
00:00:06.900 --> 00:00:10.480
A world... Yes!

3
00:00:10.480 --> 00:00:16.530
A world for you who seek freedom stretches out right before your eyes.

4
00:00:16.530 --> 00:00:20.410
If you feel guided by endless dreams,

5
00:00:20.410 --> 00:00:25.170
surpass them, flying the flag of your beliefs!

6
00:00:29.800 --> 00:00:35.480
I've just now begun to search, over the splashing waves

7
00:00:29.820 --> 00:00:35.500
Boku wa ima sagashi hajimeta mizushibuki agete

8
00:00:35.480 --> 00:00:38.630
For the everlasting world

9
00:00:35.500 --> 00:00:38.650
Hateshinaku tsudzuku sekai he

10
00:00:39.930 --> 00:00:42.990
With this overflowing passion in my chest,

11
00:00:39.950 --> 00:00:45.090
Afuredasu jounetsu wo mune ni doko made mo yuku yo

12
00:00:42.990 --> 00:00:45.070
I will go anywhere

13
00:00:45.070 --> 00:00:53.380
Seeking the light yet unseen

14
00:00:45.090 --> 00:00:53.400
Mada minu HIKARI motome

15
00:00:53.380 --> 00:00:58.940
When the summer sun stirs my heart's sails

16
00:00:53.400 --> 00:00:58.960
Natsu-iro taiyou ga KOKORO no ho wo yuraseba

17
00:00:58.420 --> 00:01:03.530
(Fly away glum blue sea...)

18
00:01:03.400 --> 00:01:09.130
That's the signal to open the door to a new world

19
00:01:03.420 --> 00:01:09.150
Atarashii sekai he no tobira wo hiraku aizu

20
00:01:08.550 --> 00:01:13.070
(Fly away glum blue sky...)

21
00:01:13.050 --> 00:01:18.060
Swaying on the waves, reaching beyond despair

22
00:01:13.070 --> 00:01:18.080
Namima ni yureteru zetsubou wo nukete

23
00:01:18.060 --> 00:01:25.530
Aiming for the other side of the horizon

24
00:01:18.080 --> 00:01:25.550
Suiheisen no mukougawa mezashite

25
00:01:25.660 --> 00:01:31.330
I've just now begun to search, over the splashing waves

26
00:01:25.680 --> 00:01:31.350
Boku wa ima sagashi hajimeta mizushibuki agete

27
00:01:31.330 --> 00:01:34.510
For the everlasting world

28
00:01:31.350 --> 00:01:34.530
Hateshinaku tsudzuku sekai he

29
00:01:35.820 --> 00:01:40.990
Afuredasu jounetsu wo mune ni doko made mo yuku yo

30
00:01:35.950 --> 00:01:38.860
With this overflowing passion in my chest

31
00:01:38.860 --> 00:01:40.970
I will go anywhere

32
00:01:40.970 --> 00:01:47.560
Seeking the light yet unseen

33
00:01:40.990 --> 00:01:47.290
Mada minu HIKARI motome

34
00:01:49.760 --> 00:01:54.090
Divine Reckoning

35
00:01:54.090 --> 00:01:55.550
There's a god?!

36
00:01:56.850 --> 00:01:59.890
In a place we're
forbidden from entering?

37
00:02:03.160 --> 00:02:06.840
Yes. Skypiea is known as God Land,

38
00:02:06.840 --> 00:02:11.280
and ruling over it is
the almighty God Enel.

39
00:02:11.280 --> 00:02:13.450
An almighty god...?

40
00:02:15.200 --> 00:02:18.750
God Enel is all-knowing.

41
00:02:18.750 --> 00:02:20.450
All-knowing?

42
00:02:20.450 --> 00:02:23.920
He also watches us
closely at all times.

43
00:02:23.920 --> 00:02:25.100
A-At all times?!

44
00:02:25.100 --> 00:02:26.330
Now, too?

45
00:02:26.330 --> 00:02:27.290
Of course.

46
00:02:30.460 --> 00:02:34.730
The sacred ground,
Upper Yard, is forbidden.

47
00:02:36.890 --> 00:02:39.390
So there's solid ground
on the sky island...

48
00:02:44.440 --> 00:02:48.360
So. There's a place we're forbidden
from entering, no matter what?

49
00:02:48.740 --> 00:02:50.800
Ah! Hey, Luffy!

50
00:02:50.800 --> 00:02:54.400
What are you thinking about now?!
You need to listen to her!

51
00:02:54.400 --> 00:02:56.420
"Forbidden from entering" means

52
00:02:56.420 --> 00:02:59.830
we're absolutely not
supposed to go there, Luffy!

53
00:02:59.830 --> 00:03:05.790
Ahh, so... there's a place
we're not supposed to go.

54
00:03:07.880 --> 00:03:12.170
I see. A place that we're absolutely
not supposed to go, huh?

55
00:03:13.210 --> 00:03:15.340
– He's itching to go.
– He's itching to go.

56
00:03:17.920 --> 00:03:20.180
Hm? But isn't this god a good guy

57
00:03:20.180 --> 00:03:24.480
who'll forgive you even if you go
somewhere you're not supposed to?

58
00:03:24.480 --> 00:03:29.180
That's... But breaking God's rules
is blasphemous, so...

59
00:03:30.340 --> 00:03:33.340
Hmm, I see. Well, I guess
it doesn't matter either way.

60
00:03:34.810 --> 00:03:37.610
Because he'd go even if
he won't be forgiven.

61
00:03:37.610 --> 00:03:39.830
Nami my sweet!

62
00:03:38.740 --> 00:03:41.450
Anyway, let's go there
to look for Nami!

63
00:03:39.830 --> 00:03:44.040
Stay where you are and don't go anywhere!

64
00:03:41.450 --> 00:03:44.290
Are you actually going
there to look for Nami?

65
00:03:44.040 --> 00:03:46.910
Nami my sweet!

66
00:03:44.290 --> 00:03:46.910
Isn't it really so you can
go to the forbidden land?!

67
00:03:51.020 --> 00:03:54.880
What's with the huge trees?

68
00:03:54.880 --> 00:03:56.590
I've never seen ones this size.

69
00:03:56.590 --> 00:03:59.890
How old are these trees?
Several hundred years?

70
00:04:00.250 --> 00:04:02.320
All these trees...

71
00:04:04.270 --> 00:04:06.560
I can't see the top of them!

72
00:04:09.060 --> 00:04:10.350
Hey, Luffy! Let's go!

73
00:04:10.670 --> 00:04:13.570
Mmm... hold on a second.
I need to finish this first.

74
00:04:13.570 --> 00:04:16.410
What if something happens to Nami

75
00:04:16.410 --> 00:04:19.200
while you're sitting
around doing nothing?!

76
00:04:19.200 --> 00:04:21.200
Just leave it! We're coming right back!

77
00:04:21.480 --> 00:04:24.040
Mmm-mmm! Hold on!
Gotta eat this one too.

78
00:04:25.370 --> 00:04:28.250
Conis, we'll be here
till night at this rate.

79
00:04:28.250 --> 00:04:30.500
I need you to show me to Upper Yard!

80
00:04:30.500 --> 00:04:32.590
What? B-But...

81
00:04:32.590 --> 00:04:33.670
Hm?

82
00:04:33.670 --> 00:04:38.220
...we don't really know
if she was even headed there.

83
00:04:38.220 --> 00:04:39.680
Plus...

84
00:04:41.820 --> 00:04:46.140
if we incur the wrath of God Enel,
then we're all doomed!

85
00:04:48.160 --> 00:04:49.190
Help!

86
00:04:53.880 --> 00:04:54.480
Help!

87
00:05:37.200 --> 00:05:39.740
Tch! That son of a bitch.
He stole my prey!

88
00:05:42.030 --> 00:05:44.700
What's going on? I hear something...

89
00:05:45.080 --> 00:05:46.010
What's happening...?

90
00:05:49.200 --> 00:05:50.580
Just give up!

91
00:05:52.580 --> 00:05:55.290
You should, too. He's mine.

92
00:05:55.290 --> 00:05:56.790
Stay out of my way!

93
00:05:57.700 --> 00:05:59.090
Same to you!

94
00:06:09.890 --> 00:06:12.610
Wh-What in the world...?

95
00:06:13.190 --> 00:06:16.900
What's going on... in this forest?!

96
00:06:17.220 --> 00:06:20.780
So, this is your old waver.

97
00:06:20.780 --> 00:06:23.530
Quite the relic you have here.

98
00:06:23.530 --> 00:06:26.000
We found it in the sea below.

99
00:06:26.000 --> 00:06:30.580
Do you mind if I take a look?
If it can be fixed, I'll do the repairs.

100
00:06:30.580 --> 00:06:34.330
I'm a dial craft engineer.

101
00:07:18.500 --> 00:07:20.460
Wh-What?! What?!

102
00:07:23.920 --> 00:07:25.920
Hey! Help me!

103
00:07:25.920 --> 00:07:27.180
Let me on!

104
00:07:28.430 --> 00:07:31.930
Uh... let you on?
But this is a one-person craft...

105
00:07:31.930 --> 00:07:33.140
Please!

106
00:07:33.140 --> 00:07:35.940
I don't know if this thing
can handle another person...

107
00:07:35.940 --> 00:07:39.230
I-I'll kill you if necessary...!

108
00:07:39.230 --> 00:07:39.770
Ahh!

109
00:07:40.690 --> 00:07:41.940
A guerrilla!

110
00:07:49.870 --> 00:07:51.690
G-God...

111
00:08:06.720 --> 00:08:09.680
Damn! Is this Enel's doing?!

112
00:08:18.720 --> 00:08:21.350
How dare you harm our vearth?!

113
00:09:03.900 --> 00:09:05.440
Get some water dials, quick!

114
00:09:06.570 --> 00:09:07.870
Put out the fire!

115
00:09:09.610 --> 00:09:13.280
Lovely Street
Angel Island

116
00:09:12.760 --> 00:09:15.030
Squad, attention!

117
00:09:15.660 --> 00:09:16.740
– Heso!
– Heso!

118
00:09:19.000 --> 00:09:21.670
Captain McKinley
White Berets, Skypiea Police

119
00:09:20.010 --> 00:09:21.670
Heso, everyone!

120
00:09:21.960 --> 00:09:23.670
That's the White Berets!

121
00:09:24.170 --> 00:09:26.000
I wonder if something happened.

122
00:09:26.500 --> 00:09:29.010
Everyone, please be careful!

123
00:09:29.010 --> 00:09:33.970
Illegal entrants have infiltrated
Skypiea through Angel Beach today!

124
00:09:33.970 --> 00:09:35.300
– What?!
– What?!

125
00:09:35.300 --> 00:09:37.770
The report told of seven infiltrators!

126
00:09:37.770 --> 00:09:42.810
We, the White Berets, are conducting
a full-scale search for these criminals!

127
00:09:42.810 --> 00:09:45.120
Keep an eye out for
suspicious individuals!

128
00:09:47.270 --> 00:09:48.440
– Keep an eye out!
– Keep an eye out!

129
00:09:49.260 --> 00:09:53.660
It looked like that man
was talking to someone.

130
00:09:53.660 --> 00:09:55.820
Probably that guerrilla
who just ran off.

131
00:09:55.820 --> 00:09:58.590
Hey, shut that dog up.

132
00:09:58.590 --> 00:10:01.160
He was probably begging for his life.

133
00:10:01.960 --> 00:10:06.950
But why would the almighty Enel
take out that man on his own?

134
00:10:06.950 --> 00:10:08.430
Did we even need to be–

135
00:10:08.430 --> 00:10:10.570
We probably ran out of time.

136
00:10:10.570 --> 00:10:11.630
Ran out of time?

137
00:10:12.320 --> 00:10:15.980
Another group of illegal entrants
has already infiltrated this land.

138
00:10:15.980 --> 00:10:18.000
Hm? Again?

139
00:10:18.000 --> 00:10:23.100
Old lady Amazon reported a ship
with seven Blue Sea people on board.

140
00:10:23.100 --> 00:10:27.230
Seven Blue Sea people...
Could he mean us?!

141
00:10:27.230 --> 00:10:28.860
He said illegal entrants...

142
00:10:29.360 --> 00:10:31.240
If you're going to the upper area,

143
00:10:31.240 --> 00:10:35.110
pay the entrance fee
of one billion extol per person.

144
00:10:35.110 --> 00:10:36.970
That is the law.

145
00:10:38.780 --> 00:10:41.920
Could it be because we
didn't pay the entrance fee?

146
00:10:41.920 --> 00:10:43.000
No way!

147
00:10:43.720 --> 00:10:47.580
Seven heads... We can't
divide them by four.

148
00:10:48.990 --> 00:10:51.670
What just happened?

149
00:10:51.670 --> 00:10:53.300
Who are these people?!

150
00:10:54.030 --> 00:10:55.660
And what is this place?!

151
00:11:04.770 --> 00:11:07.400
I have to tell everyone immediately!

152
00:11:07.400 --> 00:11:09.270
This place is crazy!

153
00:11:16.280 --> 00:11:18.250
Hey, Usopp! Check it out!

154
00:11:20.580 --> 00:11:22.660
Mine's finished, too!

155
00:11:23.920 --> 00:11:27.850
Check out my art, will ya?!
Don't they look just like us?

156
00:11:28.430 --> 00:11:29.670
That's amazing!

157
00:11:30.170 --> 00:11:32.960
Just how does that look like us?!

158
00:11:32.960 --> 00:11:34.050
Can it be fixed?

159
00:11:34.050 --> 00:11:36.800
I've never seen these parts.

160
00:11:36.800 --> 00:11:38.340
You've gotta fix it, though!

161
00:11:38.340 --> 00:11:42.560
I'm sorry, but I can't say much
until I investigate it more.

162
00:11:42.560 --> 00:11:43.940
Sure, but please try.

163
00:11:43.940 --> 00:11:45.520
I'll try disassembling it.

164
00:11:51.560 --> 00:11:53.470
Old guy, what's that?

165
00:12:00.640 --> 00:12:03.660
You there, with the suspicious
ship... Don't move!

166
00:12:03.660 --> 00:12:05.960
Who are those guys?

167
00:12:18.250 --> 00:12:20.960
Why the heck are they crawling?

168
00:12:20.960 --> 00:12:21.900
I don't know.

169
00:12:22.410 --> 00:12:25.390
They're probably... weirdos!

170
00:12:25.390 --> 00:12:27.710
What?! So those are weirdos...

171
00:12:28.800 --> 00:12:31.770
Everyone, halt!

172
00:12:34.900 --> 00:12:35.690
– Heso!
– Heso!

173
00:12:35.690 --> 00:12:36.440
Heso!

174
00:12:36.440 --> 00:12:37.650
Why, heso!

175
00:12:38.900 --> 00:12:41.740
H-Hey, what are you guys saying?!

176
00:12:41.740 --> 00:12:43.870
Who are they?

177
00:12:43.870 --> 00:12:45.580
Weirdos, apparently.

178
00:12:45.830 --> 00:12:52.500
So you're the seven illegal entrants
who came from the Blue Sea?!

179
00:12:52.500 --> 00:12:53.420
– What?!
– What?!

180
00:12:53.420 --> 00:12:56.840
I'll humbly bring
Divine Reckoning upon you!

181
00:12:57.660 --> 00:12:59.090
Illegal entrants?!

182
00:12:59.090 --> 00:13:00.590
Huh? What's that mean?

183
00:13:01.400 --> 00:13:03.500
Spare us your excuses.

184
00:13:03.500 --> 00:13:08.810
Inspector Amazon took these
vision dial pictures at Heaven's Gate.

185
00:13:08.810 --> 00:13:11.810
Oh, no! That can't be true!

186
00:13:11.810 --> 00:13:14.280
Could there be some mistake,
Captain McKinley?!

187
00:13:14.280 --> 00:13:17.070
They're not bad people like you say.

188
00:13:17.600 --> 00:13:19.860
What do you mean by "illegal entry"?

189
00:13:19.860 --> 00:13:23.350
Wasn't the entrance fee
one billion extol per person?

190
00:13:23.350 --> 00:13:25.270
It's true that we didn't pay that.

191
00:13:25.270 --> 00:13:29.300
But the old lady said we could
pass without paying, didn't she?

192
00:13:29.300 --> 00:13:30.330
She sure did!

193
00:13:30.330 --> 00:13:31.640
Give it up.

194
00:13:31.640 --> 00:13:34.420
Instead of making excuses,
admit to your guilt.

195
00:13:34.420 --> 00:13:37.300
However, there's no need to panic yet.

196
00:13:37.750 --> 00:13:43.300
Divine Reckoning establishes illegal entry
as a mere eleventh-degree crime.

197
00:13:43.300 --> 00:13:47.970
Once you receive punishment,
your tourist status becomes legal.

198
00:13:47.970 --> 00:13:50.380
Oh, you should've said so sooner.

199
00:13:50.380 --> 00:13:53.520
I hate to ask, but just
what is this punishment?

200
00:13:53.520 --> 00:13:57.980
It's simple. Please pay
ten times the entrance fee.

201
00:13:58.940 --> 00:14:04.450
If you pay right now,
we'll humbly write off your crime.

202
00:14:04.450 --> 00:14:06.160
Ten billion extol per person,

203
00:14:06.160 --> 00:14:09.330
in other words, seventy billion extol
for all seven of you.

204
00:14:09.330 --> 00:14:11.710
S-Seventy billion extol?!

205
00:14:11.710 --> 00:14:15.540
S-So how much is one extol in belly?

206
00:14:15.540 --> 00:14:18.240
Belly... That's the Blue Sea's
currency, right?

207
00:14:18.240 --> 00:14:21.510
Ten thousand extol is one belly.

208
00:14:21.510 --> 00:14:23.650
Ten thousand extol is one belly...

209
00:14:23.650 --> 00:14:24.010
1...

210
00:14:24.010 --> 00:14:24.260
10...

211
00:14:24.260 --> 00:14:24.640
100...

212
00:14:24.640 --> 00:14:25.220
1,000...

213
00:14:25.220 --> 00:14:25.510
10,000...

214
00:14:25.510 --> 00:14:26.510
100,000...

215
00:14:26.510 --> 00:14:27.600
How much is that?

216
00:14:27.600 --> 00:14:31.160
It means 70 billion extol
is 7 million belly.

217
00:14:31.160 --> 00:14:32.310
That's too expensive!

218
00:14:32.310 --> 00:14:34.850
C'mon, do you know how much
rice that could buy us?

219
00:14:34.850 --> 00:14:36.940
We risked our lives getting to the sky,

220
00:14:36.940 --> 00:14:40.230
so why do we have to pay
that much for an entrance fee?!

221
00:14:40.230 --> 00:14:41.490
That's unacceptable!

222
00:14:41.490 --> 00:14:43.570
What are you saying?

223
00:14:43.570 --> 00:14:48.200
You wouldn't even be in this position
if you had paid the 700,000 belly.

224
00:14:48.200 --> 00:14:50.490
Even that's still too expensive!

225
00:14:51.790 --> 00:14:53.410
Consider this a forewarning,

226
00:14:53.410 --> 00:14:57.000
but we, the White Berets, are the unit
directly under the priests.

227
00:14:57.000 --> 00:14:59.710
Please know, arguing raises
the degree of your crime.

228
00:14:59.710 --> 00:15:02.340
Oh, whatever.
Let's just forget this guy.

229
00:15:02.340 --> 00:15:06.540
More importantly, we'd better
go find Nami. I'm worried.

230
00:15:06.540 --> 00:15:08.350
She could be alone and crying...!

231
00:15:17.020 --> 00:15:21.220
Those guys earlier knew that
we came to the sky island,

232
00:15:21.220 --> 00:15:24.010
meaning the others
might already be in trouble.

233
00:15:24.010 --> 00:15:25.070
I have to hurry!

234
00:15:29.020 --> 00:15:31.050
I can't wait to ride it!

235
00:15:31.050 --> 00:15:32.910
I hope you can fix it.

236
00:15:33.220 --> 00:15:34.330
Oh?

237
00:15:34.740 --> 00:15:37.710
That waver looks broken.

238
00:15:37.710 --> 00:15:40.790
If you broke it,
that's a tenth-degree crime:

239
00:15:41.170 --> 00:15:44.800
the destruction of sky island property
by Blue Sea people.

240
00:15:44.800 --> 00:15:48.640
No, no! I'm sorry. It was
already theirs to begin with.

241
00:15:48.640 --> 00:15:50.300
He's right! This is mine!

242
00:15:50.620 --> 00:15:52.220
"To begin with"?

243
00:15:52.220 --> 00:15:53.870
That's suspicious.

244
00:15:53.870 --> 00:15:56.480
Wavers shouldn't exist in the Blue Sea.

245
00:15:56.480 --> 00:16:01.230
If you stole this from a sky island,
the degree of your crime will increase.

246
00:16:01.230 --> 00:16:03.570
Shut up! I'll kick your ass!

247
00:16:07.230 --> 00:16:10.150
Oh, no...! There's
already someone there!

248
00:16:10.150 --> 00:16:12.160
Maybe it's the people I saw earlier.

249
00:16:12.160 --> 00:16:16.530
Please don't do anything stupid, guys!

250
00:16:16.530 --> 00:16:18.670
Luffy, Zoro... let's reconsider this!

251
00:16:18.670 --> 00:16:21.750
Listen. You know snails,
right? They're...

252
00:16:19.960 --> 00:16:21.750
Hold on a second!

253
00:16:22.460 --> 00:16:25.420
Ah! Nami, you're all right!

254
00:16:25.420 --> 00:16:28.970
Luffy! Don't cause trouble
with those people!

255
00:16:28.970 --> 00:16:31.140
But these guys...!

256
00:16:31.140 --> 00:16:32.180
Nami!

257
00:16:32.180 --> 00:16:36.850
We need seven million belly from your
secret stash to pay for our illegal entry!

258
00:16:36.850 --> 00:16:40.210
Good! We can still
get by with a fine, then?!

259
00:16:41.470 --> 00:16:44.360
Did he just say seven million belly...?

260
00:16:47.040 --> 00:16:48.320
What?!

261
00:16:48.950 --> 00:16:50.320
That's too expensive!

262
00:16:58.000 --> 00:16:59.460
Oh, shoot!

263
00:16:59.460 --> 00:17:01.750
That price was way
too high, so I just...

264
00:17:01.750 --> 00:17:02.790
– Hey!
– Hey!

265
00:17:02.790 --> 00:17:04.250
– Captain!
– Captain!

266
00:17:04.250 --> 00:17:08.170
Hey, mister, thanks for letting me
use your waver. It was fun.

267
00:17:08.170 --> 00:17:10.030
No, no. I'm sorry.

268
00:17:10.030 --> 00:17:12.720
More importantly,
you all are in big trouble!

269
00:17:12.720 --> 00:17:14.940
Captain! Please hang in there!

270
00:17:13.560 --> 00:17:14.980
Time to go, everyone!

271
00:17:14.930 --> 00:17:15.920
It's just a flesh wound!

272
00:17:14.980 --> 00:17:17.630
Why? I thought you started a fight.

273
00:17:15.920 --> 00:17:18.960
How did this happen?! Captain!

274
00:17:17.630 --> 00:17:21.230
It's dangerous to get involved
with this God guy. Seriously!

275
00:17:21.230 --> 00:17:25.270
I believe it's a fifth-degree crime
to obstruct official duties.

276
00:17:25.570 --> 00:17:28.300
When it's determined to be
a fifth-degree crime,

277
00:17:28.300 --> 00:17:31.660
in the name of God Enel,
you'll be sent to the clouds.

278
00:17:31.660 --> 00:17:33.160
Sent to the clouds?

279
00:17:33.160 --> 00:17:36.870
What's that? Being sent
to the clouds sounds kinda nice.

280
00:17:36.870 --> 00:17:39.410
Well, it shouldn't! It means death!

281
00:17:40.490 --> 00:17:45.410
You and your ship are banished
to an inescapable island cloud

282
00:17:45.410 --> 00:17:48.170
that will keep wandering
until only your bones remain.

283
00:17:49.590 --> 00:17:51.170
It's the death penalty!

284
00:17:51.550 --> 00:17:55.200
I see. That's why that ship
fell from the sky.

285
00:17:55.200 --> 00:17:57.310
What?! What're you
talking about, Robin?

286
00:17:57.600 --> 00:18:02.400
Remember that galleon that fell
from the sky? The Saint Briss, was it?

287
00:18:02.400 --> 00:18:06.190
They might have received that
punishment 200 years ago.

288
00:18:11.530 --> 00:18:13.240
– Hey, you!
– Hey, you!

289
00:18:13.240 --> 00:18:15.740
Do you realize what you've
done to the captain?!

290
00:18:15.740 --> 00:18:18.240
Wanna choose your words better?!

291
00:18:16.530 --> 00:18:18.240
Ah! Sanji, hold on!

292
00:18:18.240 --> 00:18:19.490
Why, sure, Nami!

293
00:18:19.490 --> 00:18:22.370
Please calm down.
It was an accident.

294
00:18:22.370 --> 00:18:23.580
An accident?!

295
00:18:23.580 --> 00:18:25.580
Well, I mean, it was unintentional...

296
00:18:25.580 --> 00:18:26.710
Unintentional?!

297
00:18:26.710 --> 00:18:29.740
That's why beginners need
to take things slowly, am I right?

298
00:18:31.630 --> 00:18:35.040
Actually, she rode it pretty well,
and she looked like she had fun.

299
00:18:35.970 --> 00:18:37.330
Hey, Luffy!

300
00:18:37.330 --> 00:18:39.520
Oh, no, Luffy!

301
00:18:37.600 --> 00:18:41.730
Nami's making them think it was all
an accident, so let her do the talking!

302
00:18:39.520 --> 00:18:41.770
That's impossible!

303
00:18:41.730 --> 00:18:42.770
Oh, really?

304
00:18:43.340 --> 00:18:48.970
Um, I'm sorry, but I thought it'd be
better to treat Captain McKinley first.

305
00:18:48.970 --> 00:18:50.230
I'm sorry.

306
00:18:50.230 --> 00:18:51.780
Th-That's right!

307
00:18:51.780 --> 00:18:53.280
Captain McKinley!

308
00:18:53.280 --> 00:18:55.910
Then, let's carry him
over to my house.

309
00:18:55.910 --> 00:18:57.160
Much appreciated!

310
00:18:57.160 --> 00:18:58.120
– Heso!
– Heso!

311
00:19:00.910 --> 00:19:04.960
All seven of you, don't go
anywhere! Understood?!

312
00:19:04.960 --> 00:19:07.330
Captain!

313
00:19:08.200 --> 00:19:10.680
They're crawling again?

314
00:19:10.680 --> 00:19:12.300
Just carry him normally!

315
00:19:12.800 --> 00:19:16.390
I know you're not bad people.

316
00:19:16.390 --> 00:19:19.140
So, please use this chance
to get away from here!

317
00:19:19.140 --> 00:19:20.010
H-Hey!

318
00:19:21.780 --> 00:19:23.820
We should follow her advice.

319
00:19:24.860 --> 00:19:29.020
I saw it with my own eyes:
an island with really scary guys on it!

320
00:19:29.610 --> 00:19:33.050
So you really did go to
the forbidden sacred ground.

321
00:19:33.050 --> 00:19:36.120
"The place we're
forbidden from entering!"

322
00:19:36.120 --> 00:19:37.690
"Scary guys"!

323
00:19:37.690 --> 00:19:39.780
Ah! Don't listen! Don't look! Don't talk!

324
00:19:39.780 --> 00:19:41.740
God... guerrilla...

325
00:19:41.740 --> 00:19:44.290
No good will come from going there!

326
00:19:44.290 --> 00:19:46.250
That means we're leaving! Leaving!

327
00:19:46.870 --> 00:19:49.800
Ahh... It's heartbreaking
to be apart from Conis,

328
00:19:49.800 --> 00:19:51.410
but if that's what Nami says...

329
00:19:52.410 --> 00:19:56.220
If we stick around, those two
may also get in trouble.

330
00:19:56.220 --> 00:19:57.300
That's right!

331
00:19:57.300 --> 00:20:00.510
They'll definitely make those two out
to be our accomplices!

332
00:20:00.510 --> 00:20:03.470
So if we can show that we're
running away on our own,

333
00:20:03.470 --> 00:20:05.880
it shouldn't cause
any trouble for them.

334
00:20:05.880 --> 00:20:08.940
Right?! Okay, that settles it! Let's go!

335
00:20:14.250 --> 00:20:16.490
What are you doing, Luffy?!

336
00:20:16.490 --> 00:20:17.780
Why are we running away?

337
00:20:18.160 --> 00:20:20.070
Those two have done nothing wrong.

338
00:20:20.730 --> 00:20:22.950
The guys who arrest them are wrong.

339
00:20:25.900 --> 00:20:28.420
Please... hurry up!

340
00:20:31.310 --> 00:20:33.460
There's no place
for them to escape to.

341
00:20:35.880 --> 00:20:38.430
Wrap up your argument
and come aboard already!

342
00:20:38.430 --> 00:20:40.590
What will it take
for you to understand?!

343
00:20:40.590 --> 00:20:44.600
If we stay here, it'll be a big problem,
for us, and for those two!

344
00:20:44.600 --> 00:20:46.270
It's big trouble either way.

345
00:20:46.890 --> 00:20:48.230
Please run!

346
00:20:49.060 --> 00:20:50.350
Hurry!

347
00:20:50.350 --> 00:20:51.900
Oh, great!

348
00:20:51.900 --> 00:20:54.040
That's quite enough, miss.

349
00:20:54.040 --> 00:20:57.100
If you say anything
in defense of these criminals...

350
00:20:57.100 --> 00:21:00.420
you two are also going to pay.

351
00:21:00.420 --> 00:21:05.080
As you know, these are felons
who should be punished.

352
00:21:05.080 --> 00:21:08.830
For abusive language toward us
and obstruction of official duties...

353
00:21:08.830 --> 00:21:13.500
their sentence is fifth-degree punishment:
they will be sent to the clouds!

354
00:21:15.130 --> 00:21:17.530
Like I said, it was an accident!

355
00:21:17.530 --> 00:21:18.300
C'mon, already!

356
00:21:18.300 --> 00:21:19.930
Arrest them!

357
00:21:21.300 --> 00:21:23.300
Please run!
You're no match for them!

358
00:21:25.850 --> 00:21:26.600
Fire!

359
00:21:26.600 --> 00:21:27.930
Milky Arrows!

360
00:21:28.930 --> 00:21:29.980
Arrows?!

361
00:21:29.980 --> 00:21:31.350
You go ahead, Nami!

362
00:21:31.350 --> 00:21:32.770
Okay!

363
00:21:35.900 --> 00:21:38.450
What're these?! Clouds?!

364
00:21:41.920 --> 00:21:44.730
Go, White Berets!

365
00:21:56.030 --> 00:21:57.550
What?! What's going on?!

366
00:22:06.560 --> 00:22:08.560
You guys have some fun stuff!

367
00:22:08.560 --> 00:22:09.560
What?!

368
00:22:09.560 --> 00:22:10.930
What is he?!

369
00:22:10.930 --> 00:22:13.230
What?! His arm... His arm stretched!

370
00:22:13.230 --> 00:22:14.440
Oh, my...

371
00:22:16.620 --> 00:22:19.470
Gum-Gum...

372
00:22:20.030 --> 00:22:22.400
No way! A devil fruit!

373
00:22:24.820 --> 00:22:26.890
...Fireworks!

374
00:23:01.470 --> 00:23:03.400
By the way, Nami!

375
00:23:03.770 --> 00:23:06.260
What's our financial situation?

376
00:23:06.260 --> 00:23:07.980
We have 50,000 belly left.

377
00:23:07.980 --> 00:23:10.830
Just 50,000? We're that poor?

378
00:23:10.830 --> 00:23:14.190
Normally, that'll last
a day or two at most.

379
00:23:14.190 --> 00:23:16.620
Why are we so poor?

380
00:23:16.620 --> 00:23:18.960
As your captain, I gotta say this:

381
00:23:18.960 --> 00:23:22.260
You should give more thought about
how you use our money, and–

382
00:23:22.260 --> 00:23:23.840
It's all your meal expenses!

383
00:23:24.550 --> 00:23:25.930
Alright!

384
00:23:25.930 --> 00:23:30.160
The "Formation B" I taught them
was a huge success in battle!

385
00:23:30.160 --> 00:23:31.260
Really?!

386
00:23:31.720 --> 00:23:33.600
The White Berets...

387
00:23:33.600 --> 00:23:34.810
...were defeated!

388
00:23:35.370 --> 00:23:40.270
Normally, the athletic abilities
of Blue Sea people decrease up here.

389
00:23:46.220 --> 00:23:49.020
You fools!

390
00:23:49.020 --> 00:23:51.200
You can't go back now!

391
00:23:51.980 --> 00:23:56.120
You should've just behaved
and done what I told you to...

392
00:23:56.120 --> 00:23:58.420
We, the White Berets,

393
00:23:58.420 --> 00:24:02.130
are the most humane
law enforcers in God Land.

394
00:24:02.130 --> 00:24:05.550
However, they are nowhere
as near as gentle as we are.

395
00:24:08.080 --> 00:24:11.470
You are now second-degree criminals!

396
00:24:11.800 --> 00:24:13.980
No matter if you cry or scream...

397
00:24:16.940 --> 00:24:20.270
you'll be judged...

398
00:24:21.500 --> 00:24:23.810
by the priests of Upper Yard!

399
00:24:23.810 --> 00:24:25.490
Heso!
